LAGOS – While expectations were rife that the 2019/2020 season of the Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) will start on the weekend of August 16 and 17, the League Management Company, the organisers of the domestic league, has announced September 2 as the kick off date. The LMC, in a letter dispatched to all the participating clubs, stated that the abridged league format had been abolished to give room for the regular 38-match league. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network A provision for the league to go on break between December 30, 2019 and January 10, 2020 was also made to enable players and management spend the Yuletide season with their families. The regular season has also been scheduled to end on May 17, 2020, in order to give room for early preparations for the 2020/21 season.